HEADWORD: Pyrothonide
<hw>Py*roth"o*nide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pyro-</ets> + Gr. <?/ linen.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A
kind of empyreumatic oil produced by the combustion of textures of hemp,
linen, or cotton in a copper vessel, -- formerly used as a remedial
agent.</def> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pyrotic</ent>⟦br⟧
